cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on user reactions to transparent systems and explores user-centric methods for understanding how algorithmic decisions are made. This suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses potential errors in the system, which could fall under cybersecurity (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the need for transparency in decision-making, which could relate to cyberlaw and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
